<TITLE> HC begins to give rule on CHT accord </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Monday began giving verdict on a writ petition challenging the legality of the Chittagong Hill Tracts (CHT) accord. The bench of justices Syed Refaat Ahmed and Moyeenul Islam Chowdhury started giving the verdict after midday. The CHT accord was signed on Dec 2, 1997. Bangali settler Md Bodiuzzaman filed a petition to the High Court challenging its legality in 2000. Supreme Court advocate Md Tazul Islam filed another petition in 2007. The High Court finished hearings on both the petitions on Mar 23. bd
